LEGACY nodded to TUCSON, "The need to monitor that rip is of paramount
importance." He said solemly, his single optic flickering
thoughtfully.

At the same time RODIMUS was also nodding to TUCSON, "Yeah, let's look
around and see what we can find." Anyone loking at RODIMUS can see
that he is built something like the OPTIMAL OPTIMUS was, so he could
indeed turn into a phoenix, but it was also obvious he had other modes
as well.

LORD ELDER shook his head, "Exuse me sirs." he said as he crossed his
arms over his chest. "Shouldn't we also send out someone to try and
figure out what those Predacons were doing?" Of course he was talking
about BLIGHT and POWERPINCH who PERCEPTOR and WINDLORD had seen the
humans giving energy/glowing rocks to through some sort of strange
statue.

As all of this was going on BUMP and SANTON were walking beside
NIGHTSHIFT, "We need to get you taken care of before you start trying
to do too much of anything, this could be life threatening." They were
looking at the leg.

LEO PRIME looked at STRAIGHT SHOT, "actually there has been a call out
since I arrived which is why ones like Polar Claw and his team
arrived." He directed a hand at the him standing to one side. "I hope
that if there are any others they show up soon though."

BIG CONVOY, who quite possibly outrank everyone here nodded
thoughtfully, "It is a good plan, however I have soldiers to recover."
He was referring to LONGRACK and the others that were left behind
inside MAGMATRON's base.

Grunting CONVOY continued, "I have been thinking, we passed through a
transport doorway to get off of it, so it is possible that they may
still be alive."

(TAG)

- Preston
